'''Daniel Zizmor''' is a [[Wikipedia:Storyboard|storyboard]] and [[Wikipedia:Previsualization|previsualization]] artist for ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Computer-generated imagery|CGI]]-based television series that debuted [[October 3]], [[2008]] on [[Cartoon Network]] as a continuation of the [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|film with the same name]], released 2 months prior.

Zizmor was also a layout artist for [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] and worked in the visual effects department for [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']]. While at ILM, he played [[Kit Fisto]] in numerous scenes in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].

